A MAN is due to appear in court today in connection with an alleged attempted robbery at a bookies.&nbsp;The 50-year-old was arrested after the alleged incident the Ladbrokes shop in Union Street last month.The incident is alleged to have happened at around 10am on Tuesday April 28.He was detained in police custody and is expected to appear at Glasgow Sheriff Court later today.A Police Scotland spokesman said: &quot;A 50-year-old male was arrested on the Friday May 15.&quot;A full report will also be sent to the procurator fiscal.